HEADWORD: pachometer
<hw>pa*chom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pa`chos</grk> thickness + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring thickness, as of
the glass of a mirror, or of paper; a pachymeter.</def>⟦br⟧
